i|year=2006|title=The Primacy of Politics: Social Democracy and the Making of Europe's Twentieth Century|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521817998|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bernstein|first=Eduard|translator-last=Harvey|translator-first=Edith C.|year=1907|orig-year=1899|url=https://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/bernstein/works/1899/evsoc/index.htm|title=Evolutionary Socialism|publisher=Independent Labour Party|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bevan|first=Aneurin|year=1952|title=In Place of Fear|location=New York|publisher=Simon and Schuster|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bevan|first=Aneurin|year=1961|title=In Place of Fear|edition=2nd|publisher=MacGibbon and Kee|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Boggs|first1=Carl|last2=Plotke|first2=David|year=1980|title=Politics of Eurocommunism|publisher=Black Rose Books|isbn=9780919618312|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bookchin|first=Murray|year=1998|title=The Third Revolution: Popular Movements in the Revolutionary Era|volume=2|location=London|publisher=Cassell|isbn=9780304335930|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|editor-last1=Borragan|editor-first1=Nieves Perez-Solorzano|editor-last2=Cini|editor-first2=Michelle|year=2013|title=European Union Politics|chapter=Glossary|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199694754|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bracke|first=Maud|year=2013|title=Which Socialism, Whose D\u00e9tente?: West European Communism and the Czechoslovak Crisis of 1968|publisher=Central European University Press|isbn=9786155211263|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Brandal|first1=Nik|last2=Bratberg|first2=\u00d8ivind|last3=Thorsen|first3=Dag Einar|date=21 February 2013|title=The Nordic Model of Social Democracy|publisher=Springer|isbn=9781137013279|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Braudel|first=Fernand|year=1979|title=The Wheels of Commerce: Civilization and Capitalism 15th\u201318th Century|publisher=Harper & Row|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Brockway|first=Fenner|year=1980|title=Britain's First Socialists|ref=