11}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = It's Kate's birthday and Ben tries to find the perfect birthday present.\n |LineColor = FF5C7D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 4\n |Title = Little Sister, Big City\n |DirectedBy = [[Mark Cendrowski]]\n |WrittenBy = Jared Miller\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2011|3|7}}\n |Viewers = 7.27<ref name=\"s1e04\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/03/08/monday-final-ratings-the-chicago-code-adjusted-down-two-and-a-half-men-repeat-adjusted-up-no-adjustment-for-the-event/85036|first=Robert|last=Seidman|title=Monday Final Ratings: ''The Chicago Code'' Adjusted Down; ''Two and a Half Men'' Repeat Adjusted Up; No Adjustment for ''The Event''|date=March 8, 2011|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=March 9, 2011}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary =   An overprotective Kate seems to forget that her younger sister Julia ([[Brittany Snow]]) is no longer a kid. Larry and Connie decide to be each other's wingmen.\n |LineColor = FF5C7D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 5\n |Title = To Munsch or Not to Munsch\n |DirectedBy = [[Beth McCarthy-Miller]]\n |WrittenBy = Corey Nickerson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2011|3|14}}\n |Viewers = 6.45<ref name=\"s1e05\">{{cite web|last=Gorman|first=Bill|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/03/15/monday-final-ratings-harrys-law-adjusted-up-no-adjustment-for-chuck-the-event-or-any-other-new-show/85836|title=Monday Final Ratings: 'Harry's Law' Adjusted Up; No Adjustment For 'Chuck,' 'The Event' Or Any Other New Show|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 15, 2011|accessdate=March 15, 2011}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = Ben helps Connie with her nanny job in an attempt to befriend his girlfriend's best friend. Larry breaks up with women by avoiding them until they leave him, and Kate is determined to change his ways.\n |LineColor = FF5C7D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 6\n |Title = The Spy Who Loved Me\n |DirectedBy = Rob Schiller\n |WrittenBy = Josh Malmuth\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2011|3|2