 son at her son's friend's birthday party, only to discover that the party is for Holly's daughter, Oprah Pearl.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Gives Thanks\n |Aux1=Jonathan Green & Gabe Miller\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|20}}\n |EpisodeNumber=9\n |ShortSummary=Richie and Lina break up. Meanwhile, everyone else holds their own [[Thanksgiving]] festivities.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Runs Into a Convenience Store\n |Aux1=David Crane & Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|11|27}}\n |EpisodeNumber=10\n |ShortSummary=Richie crashes his car into the local convenience store.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Celebrates an Anniversary\n |Aux1=Teleplay: Mike Sikowitz<br />Story: David Crane & Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|12|11}}\n |EpisodeNumber=11\n |ShortSummary=Yonk and Nicole celebrate their one-year wedding anniversary. Richie and Lina get back together.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Visits a Bad Neighborhood\n |Aux1=Sue Murphy\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|8}}\n |EpisodeNumber=12\n |ShortSummary=Richie, Nicole and Duncan run into Fern, who's brandishing a gun.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Hits It\n |Aux1=Doty Abrams\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|15}}\n |EpisodeNumber=13\n |ShortSummary=Richie and Lina spend their first night together.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Has to Go to a Stupid Museum\n |Aux1=Teleplay: Jonathan Green & Gabe Miller<br />Story: Corey Nickerson\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|22}}\n |EpisodeNumber=14\n |ShortSummary=Ethan and Kyle listen in on a conversation between Kat and Benjamin. Lina gets out of her wheelchair.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class