7|1|8}}\n |EpisodeNumber=12\n |ShortSummary=Richie, Nicole and Duncan run into Fern, who's brandishing a gun.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Hits It\n |Aux1=Doty Abrams\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|15}}\n |EpisodeNumber=13\n |ShortSummary=Richie and Lina spend their first night together.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Has to Go to a Stupid Museum\n |Aux1=Teleplay: Jonathan Green & Gabe Miller<br />Story: Corey Nickerson\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|1|22}}\n |EpisodeNumber=14\n |ShortSummary=Ethan and Kyle listen in on a conversation between Kat and Benjamin. Lina gets out of her wheelchair.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Eats Moroccan Chicken\n |Aux1=Teleplay: Steven Molaro<br />Story: David Crane & Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|5}}\n |EpisodeNumber=15\n |ShortSummary=Lina and Richie host their first event as a couple; Lina serves some disgusting Moroccan chicken.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Has a Snow Day\n |Aux1=Teleplay: David Crane & Jeffrey Klarik<br />Story: Mike Sikowitz\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|12}}\n |EpisodeNumber=16\n |ShortSummary=Everyone gets snowed in at each other's houses on [[Valentine's Day]].\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Springs a Leak\n |Aux1=David Crane and Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|19}}\n |EpisodeNumber=17\n |ShortSummary=Nicole floods her house trying to create a reason to keep Duncan around.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Rides a Bull \n |Aux1=Teleplay: Mike Sikowitz<br />Story: David Crane & Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|26}}\n |EpisodeNumber=18\n |ShortSummary= Nicole finally decides to leave Yonk for Duncan. To give herself time to pack, she has Duncan and Richie keep Yonk occupied with dinner at a steakhouse.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |Title=The Class Goes Back to the Hospital\n |Aux1=David Crane and Jeffrey Klarik\n |Aux2=James Burrows\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|3|5}}\n |EpisodeNumber=19\n |ShortSummary=The class returns to the hospital after Yonk has a heart attack. Series finale.\n |LineColor=E9AB55\n}}\n|}\n\n==American television ratings==\n\n===Standard ratings===\n<!-- All Information in this sub section needs to be well sourced. Could a weekly rankings column be added to the below table also. -->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Episode #\n! Title\n! Air date\n! Rating<ref name=\"your\">{{cite web |url=http://entertainmentnow.wordpress.com/ |title=Your One Stop Shop For All Things Entertainment |accessdate=October 15, 2007}}</ref>\n! Share<ref name=\"your\" />\n! 18\u201349<ref name=\"your\" />\n! Viewers<ref name=\"your\" />\n! Rank<ref>{{cite web |url=http://groups.google.com/group/rec.arts.tv/topics |title=Google Groups |accessdate=October 5, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1\n| \"The Class Reunites\"\n| September 18, 2006\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 6.9\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 11\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 3.7\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 10.60\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | #42\n|-\n| 2\n| \"The Class Visits a Hospital\"\n| September 25, 2006\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 5.7\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 2.8\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 8.51\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | #48\n|-\n| 3\n| \"The Class Learns About Hurricanes\"\n| October 2, 2006\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 5.5\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 2.8\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 8.00\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | #55\n|-\n| 4\n| \"The Class Blows the Whistle\"\n| October 9, 2006\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 6.5\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 10\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | 3.7\