\n| {{N/a}}\n| 4<ref name=\"Ratings08\" />\n| {{N/a}}\n|}\n\n==International broadcast==\nIn [[Canada]], the series airs on [[Global Television|Global]] and premiered on January 19, 2012, after ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120122034237/http://www.globaltv.com/rob/index.html \u00a1Rob! - GlobalTV.com: Official Site of Global Television]</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nReviews for ''Rob'' were generally unfavorable. Jace Lacob of ''[[The Daily Beast]]'' described it as CBS's \"worst new show\" and wrote of the first episode that \"there isn\u2019t a single Latin name among the writers or producers\" and that it \"offers a wafer-thin appreciation and awareness of Mexican culture, one that doesn\u2019t go beyond guacamole and the occasional use of the Spanish endearment ''mija'' (my daughter).\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2012/01/11/cbs-s-rob-is-tv-s-worst-new-show.html|title=CBS\u2019s \u2018Rob\u2019 Is TV\u2019s Worst New Show|last=Lacob|first=Jace|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=January 11, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref> Robert Bianco of ''[[USA Today]]'' wrote in his review that \"Some of this barrage of stereotypes might be passable if even one character were intelligently written and skillfully played, but there's hardly a moment or performance in Rob that doesn't reek of the leftover and the second-rate\" and that \"Schneider's the only actor who even seems to be trying.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/television/reviews/story/2012-01-11/Rob-review-Rob-Schneider/52508504/1|title=What's bad about 'Rob'? The whole enchilada|last=Bianco|first=Robert|work=[[USA Today]]|date=January 11, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref> In a more positive review, Glenn Garvin of ''[[The Miami Herald]]'' wrote in his review that the show is a \"rather funny sitcom about the cultural collisions that occur every day in an increasingly blended America\". The show received a 28/100 rating on [[Metacritic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/rob/critic-reviews|title=Critic Reviews for Rob Season 1|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=February 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Season ratings===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:90%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Episodes\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Time slot ([[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|ET]]/[[Pacific Time Zone|PT]])\n! colspan=\"2\" | Season premiere\n! colspan=\"2\" | Season finale\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n! style=\"background:#ffdead;\" colspan=\"2\"| Viewers<br />(millions)\n|-\n! Date\n! span style=\"width:7%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(millions)\n! Date\n! span style=\"width:10%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(millions)\n! style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | Total\n! style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | Adults<br />18\u201349\n|-\n! '''1'''\n| 8\n| Thursdays 8:30&nbsp;p.m.\n| January 12, 2012\n| 13.47<ref name=\"Ratings01\" />\n| March 1, 2012\n| 8.99<ref name=\"Ratings08\" />\n| 25th\n! style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | 12.01<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/24/complete-list-of-2011-12-season-tv-show-viewership-sunday-night-football-tops-followed-by-american-idol-ncis-dancing-with-the-stars/135785/|title=Complete List Of 2011-12 Season TV Show Viewership: 'Sunday Night Football' Tops, Followed By 'American Idol,' 'NCIS' & 'Dancing With The Stars'|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Gormam|first=Bill|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate=June 17, 2012}}</ref>\n! style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | 4.75<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/24/final-list-of-2011-12-season-tv-show-ratings-sunday-night-football-tops-followed-by-american-idol-the-voice-modern-family/135747/|title=Complete List Of 2011-12 Season TV Show Ratings: 'Sunday Night Football' Tops, Followed By 'American Idol,' 'The Voice' & 'Modern Family'|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Gorman|first=Bill|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate=June 17, 2012}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|1840429}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rob (TV Series)}}\n[[Category:2010s American sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2012 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2012 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:CBS original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by CBS Television Studios]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Latino sitcoms]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n |show_name = Rob\n |image = \n |genre = [[Sitcom]]\n |creator = {{Plain list|\n*[[Rob Schneider]]\n*[[Lewis Morton|Lew Morton]]\n}}\n |starring = {{Plain list|\n*Rob Schneider\n*[[Cheech Marin]]\n*[[Claudia Bassols]]\n*[[Diana Maria Riva]]\n*[[Eugenio Derbez]]\n*[[Lupe Ontiveros]]\n}}\n |theme_music_composer = \n |country = United States\n |language = English\n |num_seasons = 1\n |num_episodes = 8\n |list_episodes = #Episodes\n |executive_producer = {{Plain list|\n*Kim Tannenbaum\n*Eric Tannenbaum\n*Rob Schneider\n*Lew Morton\n}}\n |producer =\n |location = \n |camera = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n |runtime = 22 minutes\n |company = {{Plain list|\n*[[CBS Productions]]\n*From Out of Nowhere Productions\n*The Tannenbaum Company\n}}\n |distributor = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n |network = [[CBS]]\n |picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n |audio_format =\n |first_aired = {{start date|2012|1|12}}\n |last_aired = {{end date|2012|3|1}}\n |website = \n |website_title = Official website\n}}\n\n'''''Rob''''' (stylized in promos as '''''\u00a1Rob!''''') is an American sitcom television series that premiered on [[CBS]] on January 12, 2012, at {{nowrap|8:30 pm ([[Eastern Time Zone|ET]])}} as a [[mid-season replacement]] for ''[[Rules of Engagement (TV series)|Rules of Engagement]]'',<ref name=\"SeriesPremiere\">{{cite news |url=http://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2011/11/15/cbs-announces-new-rob-schneider-comedy-return-of-undercover-boss/ |title=CBS Announces New Rob Schneider Comedy, Return Of 'Undercover Boss' |publisher=[[CBS Los Angeles]] |date=November 15, 2011}}</ref> and ended on March 1, 2012. The series stars [[Rob Schneider]] alongside [[Cheech Marin]], [[Claudia Bassols]], [[Diana Maria Riva]], [[Eugenio Derbez]], Ricky Rico, and [[Lupe Ontiveros]]. The show was produced by ''[[Two and a Half Men]]''{{'}}s The Tannenbaum Company and [[CBS Television Studios]]. On May 13, 2012, CBS canceled the series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/05/13/unforgettable-canceled-by-cbs/133864/|title=Updated: 'Unforgettable' Canceled by CBS; 'NYC 22,' 'Rob' Too|publisher=TV by the Numbers|date=May 13, 2012|accessdate=May 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe series follows Rob ([[Rob Schneider]]), a former lifelong bachelor and [[landscape architect]] with [[Obsessive Compulsive Disorder]], who marries into a tight-knit [[Mexican American]] family and attempts to be closer to them, often ending in disastrous results despite his good intentions.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n* [[Rob Schneider]] as Rob\n* [[Claudia Bassols]] as Maggie, Rob's much-younger wife\n* [[Cheech Marin]] as Fernando, Maggie's cynical father\n* [[Diana Maria Riva]] as Rosa, Maggie's wise cracking and sarcastic mother who sees through all of Fernando's ploys\n* [[Eugenio Derbez]] as Hector, Rosa's brother, Maggie's uncle, and the self-proclaimed \"best friend\" of Rob\n* [[Lupe Ontiveros]] as Abuelita, Fernando's mother and Maggie's grandmother\n\n==Production==\nThe pilot first appeared on [[CBS]]'s development slate in October 2010.<ref>[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2010/10/28/development-update-thursday-october-28-123511/8950/ Breaking News - Development Update: Thursday, October 28 | TheFutonCritic.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> On February 4, 2011, CBS placed a pilot order, written by [[Rob Schneider]] and Lew Morton, and directed by Jamie Widdoes. The series' executive producers were Schneider, Morton, and Kim and Eric Tannenbaum.<ref>[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2011/02/04/development-update-friday-february-4-632425/9123/ Breaking News - Development Update: Friday, February 4 | TheFutonCritic.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The series then premiered {{nowrap|January 12, 2012}}, and concluded on March 1, 2012, after eight episodes.<ref name=\"8episodes\">[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/rob/listings/ Shows A-Z - rob on cbs | TheFutonCritic.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#960000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |viewers= |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 1\n|Title           = Pilot\n|DirectedBy      = [[James Widdoes]]\n|WrittenBy       = [[Lewis Morton|Lew Morton]] & [[Rob Schneider]]\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|1|12}}\n|Aux4            = 13.47<ref name=\"Ratings01\">{{Cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/01/13/thursday-final-ratings-big-bang-theory-adjusted-up-private-practice-adjusted-down/|title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'Big Bang Theory' Adjusted Up; 'Private Practice' Adjusted Down|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|last=Seidman|first=Robert|date=January 13, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = Rob meets his new wife's Mexican family, and his first day with them is a fiasco.\n|LineColor       = 960000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 2\n|Title           = Second Wedding\n|DirectedBy      = [[Andrew D. Weyman|Andrew Weyman]]\n|WrittenBy       = [[Phoef Sutton]]\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|1|19}}\n|Aux4            = 11.41<ref name=\"Ratings02\">{{Cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/01/20/thursday-final-ratings-big-bang-theory-tops-american-idol-1st-half-hour-office-mentalist-greys-adj-up-person-rob-parks-adj-down/|title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'Big Bang Theory' Tops 'American Idol' 1st Half Hour; 'Office,'