ld secret that Maggie had told to him. Wondering if Maggie has any such secrets, Rob then \"discovers\" an old picture of Maggie with a hot former boyfriend and becomes jealous, thinking he is not good enough for her.\n|LineColor       = 960000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 5\n|Title           = Rob Learns Spanish\n|DirectedBy      = [[John Whitesell]]\n|WrittenBy       = Danny Jacobson & [[Norma Safford Vela|Norma Vela]]\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|2|9}}\n|Aux4            = 10.74<ref name=\"Ratings05\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/02/10/thursday-final-ratings-the-big-bang-theory-american-idol-greys-anatomy-the-mentalist-vampire-diaries-adjusted-up-rob-private-practice-the-finder-up-all-nig/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130209223643/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/02/10/thursday-final-ratings-the-big-bang-theory-american-idol-greys-anatomy-the-mentalist-vampire-diaries-adjusted-up-rob-private-practice-the-finder-up-all-nig/|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 9, 2013|title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'The Big Bang Theory,' 'American Idol,' 'Grey's Anatomy,' 'The Mentalist,' 'Vampire Diaries' Adjusted Up; 'Rob,' 'Private Practice,' 'The Finder,' 'Up All Night' Adjusted Down|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Seidman|first=Robert|date=February 10, 2012|accessdate=February 10, 2012}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = Rob secretly asks Hector to teach him Spanish so that he can understand what Maggie's family is saying about him. Meanwhile, Fernando lies to Rosa about his diet and exercising.\n|LineColor       = 960000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 6\n|Title           = The Baby Bug\n|DirectedBy      = Andrew Weyman\n|WrittenBy       = Danny Jacobson & Norma Vela\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|2|16}}\n|Aux4            = 10.65<ref name=\"Ratings06\">{{Cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/02/17/thursday-final-ratings-american-idol-vampire-diaries-greys-anatomy-big-bang-theory-30-rock-office-adjusted-up-pe