l the things they never did together. Special guest [[Jennette McCurdy]].\n |LineColor       = 00C5CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 15\n |Title           = Father-Daughter Dance \n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = [[Michael Patrick Jann]]\n |WrittenBy       = David Feeney\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|3|18}} <small>(UK)</small><br />Unaired <small>(US)</small>\n |ProdCode        = 1AVE14\n |Viewers         = <span style=\"color: gray;\"><small>N/A</small></span> \n |ShortSummary    = The siblings' dad Randy closes a business deal with Kate's help, leaving Ben feeling sidelined. Ben tries to upstage Kate by volunteering to organise the annual father-daughter dance at Maddie's school.\n |LineColor       = 00C5CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |Title           = Ethics 101\n |RTitle          = \n |DirectedBy      = Jay Chandrasekhar\n |WrittenBy       = [[Lindsey Shockley]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|3|18}} <small>(UK)</small><br />Unaired <small>(US)</small>\n |ProdCode        = 1AVE15\n |Viewers         = <span style=\"color: gray;\"><small>N/A</small></span> \n |ShortSummary    = Kate returns to college, determined to focus on her studies instead of boys this time around. Ben is excited to celebrate his two-month anniversary with girlfriend Vera.\n |LineColor       = 00C5CD\n}}\n|}\n\n==Broadcasts==\n''Ben and Kate'' premiered in Australia on October 8, 2012 on [[Network Ten]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Channel Ten, Network 10, Clinging to the Remnants of Youth|url=http://www.theage.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/clinging-to-the-remnants-of-youth-20120914-25vmk.html|first=Michael|last=Idato|work=TheAge|date=September 17, 2012|accessdate=September 17, 2012|location=Melbourne}}</ref> The show premiered in the United Kingdom January 7, 2013 on [[ITV2]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ITV2 Acquires UK Rights To \u2019666 Park Avenue\u2019, \u2018Ben & Kate\u2019, \u2018Animal Practice\u2019 & \u2018Up All Night\u2019|url=http://www.tvwise.co.uk/2012/08/itv2-acquires-uk-rights-to-666-park-avenue-animal-practice-ben-kate-up-all-night/|first=Patrick|last=Munn|work=TVWise|date=August 23, 2012|accessdate=August 23, 2012}}</ref> In Canada, the program premiered on September 25, 2012 on [[City (TV network)|City]] in a simulcast with the U.S. showing.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2177491|Ben and Kate}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/BenandKate ''Ben and Kate''] at [[Facebook]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ben And Kate}}\n[[Category:2012 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2013 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2010s American single-camera sitcoms]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series about dysfunctional families]]\n[[Category:Television series by 20th Century Fox Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Los Angeles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Ben and Kate\n| image                = Ben&Kate promotional logo.jpg\n| caption              =\n| show_name_2          =\n| genre                = [[Sitcom]]\n| creator              = [[Dana Fox]]\n| developer            =\n| writer               =\n| director             =\n| creative_director    =\n| presenter            =\n| starring             = [[Dakota Johnson]]<br/>[[Nat Faxon]]<br/>[[Lucy Punch]]<br/>[[Maggie Elizabeth Jones]]<br/>[[Echo Kellum]]\n| narrated             =\n| theme_music_composer = [[Michael Andrews (musician)|Michael Andrews]]\n| opentheme            = \"Get Up Again\" by Michael Andrews\n| endtheme             =\n| composer             = Michael Andrews\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 16 (3 unaired in the U.S.)\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = [[Peter Chernin]]<br/>Dana Fox<br/>Katherine Pope<br/>Jake Kasdan<br/>John Quaintance<br/>David Feeney<br/>David Katzenberg\n| producer             = Megan Mascena Gaspar<br/>Sam Sklaver<br/>Randy Cordray<br/>Alex Cuthbertson<br/>Matt Fusfeld<br/>Lorena Scafaria<br/>Gail Ferner\n| editor               =\n| location             =\n| cinematography       =\n| camera               = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime              = 21\u201323 minutes\n| company              = Hemingway Drive Productions<br/>[[Chernin Entertainment]]<br/>[[20th Century Fox Television]]\n| channel              = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| picture_format       =\n| audio_format         =\n| first_run            =\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2012|9|25}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2013|1|22}}\n| preceded_by          =\n| followed_by          =\n| related              =\n| website              =\n| website_title        = Official website\n| production_website   =\n}}\n'''''Ben and Kate''''' is an American single-camera [[sitcom]] television series that ran on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] from September 25, 2012, to January 22, 2013, as part of the [[2012\u201313 United States network television schedule|2012\u201313 television season]]. The show was produced by [[20th Century Fox Television]] and Chernin Entertainment. The show was created by Dana Fox who served as an executive producer alongside [[Peter Chernin]], Katherie Pope, and [[Jake Kasdan]].\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe series focuses on a brother and sister who at first seem to be exact opposites: Ben is an over-the-top dreamer and professional underachiever, while younger sister Kate is a more practical single mother working as a bar manager. After visiting their home in [[Los Angeles]], Ben realizes that his sister needs help with her life and taking care of her six-year-old daughter, Maddie. Because of this, he moves in with Kate so he can discover some of the things he has missed out on and Kate hopes to return the favor by bringing her brother back to reality. Along the way, they are surrounded by their close friends, B.J. and Tommy.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n\n===Main cast and characters===\n*[[Dakota Johnson]] as Kate Fox, a neurotic and awkward yet earnest single mom who works as a bartender. Her college boyfriend broke up with her once she became pregnant with Maddie and she is since wary of the dating world.\n*[[Nat Faxon]] as Ben Fox, Kate's goofy older brother who moves into her house.  Despite being caught in a state of arrested development, Ben is very popular and protective of his family. He frequently tries his hand at [[inventing]] and [[entrepreneurship]], though few attempts pan out.  His ideas include \"Bunk Bed Pizza\", which makes another friend rich, and, more recently, \"Rail Mall\", which he actually focuses on turning into a reality.\n*[[Lucy Punch]] as BJ (Beatrice Joan) Harrison, Kate's much more confident best friend and co-worker.  A vain hard partier, BJ is secretly married to Ben, despite the two sharing no feelings for each other. She often lectures Maddie at a level beyond her understanding. Although she has a British accent, she reveals she's actually from Texas.\n*[[Maggie Elizabeth Jones]] as Maddie Fox, Kate's 6-year-old daughter.\n*[[Echo Kellum]] as Tommy, Ben's charismatic best friend who works at a country club as a tennis instructor. In addition to sharing many of Ben's quirks, Tommy has been in love with Kate since high school. He is also a frequent collaborator on Ben's quirky schemes and business ideas.\n\n===Recurring cast and characters===\n*[[Geoff Stults]] as Will, a friendly single dad and neighbor who briefly dates Kate. Though they have chemistry, he becomes wary of her eccentric friends and family.\n*[[Rob Corddry]] as Buddy, the boorish owner of the bar where Kate and BJ work, also BJ's on-and-off boyfriend.\n*[[Brittany Snow]] as Lila, Tommy's girlfriend.\n*[[Melinda McGraw]] as Vera, a successful businesswoman who is physically attracted to Ben and helps his \"Rail Mall\" idea become an actual business.\n*[[Lauren Miller]] as Darcy, Ben's ex, whom he is still in love with when the series begins.\n*[[Luka Jones]] as Lance, a laid-back baker who begins to date Kate after she breaks up with Will.\n*[[Bruce McGill]] as Randy, Ben and Kate's negligent yet friendly father.\n\n==Production==\n===Development and production===\nIn October 2011, Fox bought the project, titled ''Ben Fox is My Manny'', from creator [[Dana Fox]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2011/10/fox-buys-sibling-comedy-from-feature-scribe-dana-fox-with-penalty/|title=Fox Buys Sibling Comedy From Feature Writer Dana Fox With Penalty|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=25 October 2011|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> In January 2012, Fox ordered the show to pilot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/01/fox-greenlights-dana-fox-comedy-pilot/|title=Fox Greenlights Dana Fox Comedy Pilot|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=9 January 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> The show was retitled to ''Ned Fox Is My Manny'', then to ''The Kids'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.backstage.com/news/casting/fox-pilot-ned-fox-is-my-manny-gets-new-name-new-casting-directors/|title=Fox Pilot \u2018Ned Fox Is My Manny\u2019 Gets New Name, New Casting Directors|author=Keeley, Pete|date=30 March 2012|publisher=backstage.com|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> before finally being called ''Ben and Kate''. On 9 May Fox ordered the show to series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/fox-picks-up-comedy-ned-fox-is-my-manny-to-series/|title=3rd Update: Fox Picks Up Kevin Williamson, Mob Doc Drama, Three Comedy Series|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=9 May 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> On 14 May [[Neil Goldman and Garrett Donovan]] were announced as showrunners.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/two-new-comedy-series-land-showrunners/|title=Two New Comedy Series Land Showrunners|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=14 May 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref> On 11 September, it was announced that Goldman and Donovan had left the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Producer-Change-Ben-and-Kate-1052843.aspx|title=Exclusive: Producer Change at the Top of Fox\u2019s Ben and Kate|author=Schneider, Michael|date=11 September 2012|publisher=tvguide.com|accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref> Goldman and Donovan cited creative differences as their reason for leaving.<ref name=fbaktns/> On October 8, 2012, Fox ordered a full season of 19 episodes of the series, that took the series beyond its initial 13 episode order.<ref name=\"kondolojy1\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/10/08/ben-kate-the-mindy-project-get-full-season-orders/151994|title='Ben and Kate' & 'The Mindy Project' Get Full Season Orders|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 8, 2012|accessdate=October 8, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010234124/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/10/08/ben-kate-the-mindy-project-get-full-season-orders/151994/|archivedate=October 10, 2012}}</ref> On 9 November it was announced that John Quaintance and David Feeney would become the new showrunners.<ref name=fbaktns>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/foxs-ben-kate-taps-new-388085|title=Fox's 'Ben and Kate' Taps New Showrunners|author=Goldberg, Lesley|date=9 November 2012|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\n[[Maggie Elizabeth Jones]] was the first actor announced to have been cast, on February 1, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/02/pilot-castings-beautiful-people-last-resort-ben-fox-is-my-manny-set-actors/|title=PILOT CASTINGS: \u2018Beautiful People\u2019, \u2018Last Resort\u2019 & \u2018Ben Fox Is My Manny\u2019 Set Actors|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=1 February 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> On February 14, [[Echo Kellum]] was announced as Tommy, Ben's best friend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/02/michael-arden-joins-anger-management-echo-kellum-cast-in-ben-fox-is-my-manny/|title=Michael Arden Joins \u2018Anger Management\u2019, Echo Kellum Cast In \u2018Ben Fox Is My Manny\u2019|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=14 February 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> On February 23, [[Abby Elliott]] was announced to star as Kate Fox.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/02/abby-elliott-to-star-in-fox-comedy-pilot-might-leave-saturday-night-live/|title=Abby Elliott To Star In Fox Comedy Pilot, Might Leave \u2018Saturday Night Live\u2019|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=23 February 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> On February 24, [[Lucy Punch]] was announced as BJ, Kate's best friend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/02/lucy-punch-joins-ned-fox-is-my-manny-dave-annable-michael-esper-cast-in-pilots/|title=Lucy Punch Joins \u2018Ned Fox Is My Manny\u2019, Dave Annable & Michael Esper Cast In Pilots|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=24 February 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> On February 28, [[Nat Faxon]] was announced as Ben Fox.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/descendants-oscar-winner-fox-pilot-295830|title='Descendants' Oscar Winner to Star in Fox Comedy Pilot|author=Goldberg, Lesley|date=28 February 2012|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref>\nFaxon was cast days after he won an [[Academy Award]] for co-writing ''[[The Descendants]]'' (2011).<ref>{{cite news|last=de Moraes|first=Lisa|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/tv-column/post/nat-faxon-locked-to-star-in-foxs-ben-and-kate-before-he-realized-hed-made-a-huge-mistake/2012/07/24/gJQAVJyX5W_blog.html|title=Nat Faxon locked to star in Fox's 'Ben and Kate' before he realized he'd made a huge mistake |work=Washington Post|accessdate=January 23, 2013|date=24 July 2012}}</ref> On March 20, it was announced that Elliott had been released from the show after the pilot's table read.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/03/abby-elliott-exits-ned-fox-is-my-manny/|title=Abby Elliott Exits \u2018Ned Fox Is My Manny\u2019|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=20 March 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> Elliott was released because it was thought she was too young for the role.<ref name=djc/> On March 21, it was announced that [[Austin Stowell]] would appear as a guest star in the role of Ryan, a character who Kate used to have a crush on and reunites with her for a date. It was reported that it would be a recurring role if the show was picked up.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ned-fox-is-my-manny-austin-stowell-casting-302915|title='Secret Life's' Austin Stowell Joins 'Ned Fox Is My Manny' Pilot (Exclusive)|author=Nededog, Jethro|date=21 March 2012|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref> On 23 March, it was announced that [[Dakota Johnson]] would be replacing Elliott in the role of Kate Fox.<ref name=djc>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/03/dakota-johnson-cast-as-the-lead-of-fox-comedy-pilot-ned-fox-is-my-manny/|title=Dakota Johnson Cast As The Lead Of Fox Comedy Pilot \u2018Ned Fox Is My Manny\u2019|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=23 March 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nAfter the show was ordered to series, some recurring roles and guest appearances were announced. On August 14, [[Vernee Watson]] and [[Tom Wright (actor)|Tom Wright]] were announced as Tommy's parents.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ben-kate-parents-echo-kellum-361628|title='Ben and Kate': Get Ready to Meet the Parents (Exclusive)|author=Goldberg, Lesley|date=14 August 2012|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On August 20, [[Rob Corddry]] was announced as Buddy, Kate's boss and BJ's boyfriend.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/08/20/childrens-hospital-funnyman-to-join-foxs-new-comedy-ben-kate-exclusive/|title='Childrens Hospital funny man joins Fox's 'Ben & Kate'|author=Rice, Lynette|date=20 August 2012|publisher=ew.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On August 23, [[Lindsay Sloane]] was announced as Louise, an ex-girlfriend of Ben's who unexpectedly tracks him down.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/23/ben-and-kate-lindsay-sloane/|title=Exclusive: Lindsay Sloane Heads to Fox's Ben and Kate as Nat Faxon's Ex-Girlfriend|author=Ausiello, Michael|date=23 August 2012|publisher=tvline.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On September 5, [[Geoff Stults]] was announced as Will, a love interest for Kate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/09/geoff-stults-signs-talent-deal-with-20th-tv-joins-ben-kate-as-recurring/|title=Geoff Stults Signs Talent Deal With 20th TV, Joins \u2018Ben & Kate\u2019 As Recurring|author=Andreeva, Nellie|date=5 September 2012|publisher=deadline.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On November 5, [[Jane Seymour (actress)|Jane Seymour]] was announced as Wendy, BJ's mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/11/05/ben-and-kate-season-1-cast-jane-seymour-bj-mom/|title=Exclusive: Ben and Kate Recruits Jane Seymour as BJ's 'Sexy' Mom \u2014 Plus a Sunny Star Stops By|author=Gelman, Vlada|date=5 November 2012|publisher=tvline.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On November 9, [[Brittany Snow]] was announced as Lila, a love interest for Tommy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/361687/ben-and-kate-casting-scoop-brittany-snow-to-guest-star-as-a-love-interest-for|title=Ben and Kate Casting Scoop: Brittany Snow to Guest Star as a Love Interest for...|author=Bricker, Tierney|date=9 November 2012|publisher=eonline.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> On January 10, 2013 [[Niecy Nash]] was announced as Roz, the wife of Buddy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2013/01/10/ben-and-kate-season-1-cast-niecy-nash/|title=Exclusive: Ben and Kate Casts Niecy Nash to Face Off With BJ Over a Guy \u2014 Who'll Prevail?|author=Masters, Megan|date=10 January 2013|publisher=tvline.com|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nFor the most part, ''Ben and Kate'' has been moderately received, obtaining a score of 67 out of 100 on [[Metacritic]], indicating generally favorable reviews.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ben & Kate - Season 1 Review|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/ben-kate|work=Metacritic|accessdate=October 4, 2012}}</ref> It currently holds a rating of 5.3/10 on [[TV.com]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ben & Kate|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/ben-and-kate|work=TV.com|accessdate=October 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Cancellation==\nDespite the show's positive reviews, TV By the Numbers had ''Ben and Kate'' on its \"likely to be cancelled\" list, citing the show's disappointing 1.2 rating among 18- to 49-year-olds in an October 16 episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/10/23/fox-ben-and-kate-is-likely-to-be-canceled-the-extra-episodes-just-postpone-the-date/154180|title=FOX: 'Ben And Kate' Is Likely To Be Canceled, The Extra Episodes Just Postpone The Date|last=Gorman|first=Bill|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 23, 2012|accessdate=November 14, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108224629/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/10/23/fox-ben-and-kate-is-likely-to-be-canceled-the-extra-episodes-just-postpone-the-date/154180/|archive-date=November 8, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> The show faced stiff competition from CBS's ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'', NBC's ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'', and ABC's ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''.\n\nOn January 23, 2013, the show was pulled from the schedule.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/fox-pulls-ben-kate-schedule-414770|title=Fox Pulls 'Ben and Kate' From Schedule, Ditches Tuesday Comedy Block|author=O'Connell, Michael|author2=Goldberg, Lesley|date=23 January 2013|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref> On January 25, Fox confirmed that the show had been cancelled.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/fox-officially-cancels-ben-kate-415546|title=Fox Officially Cancels 'Ben and Kate,' Shuts Down Production|author=O'Connell, Michael|date=25 January 2013|publisher=hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=2 March 2013}}</ref> Of the six additional episodes ordered to take the show to a full season, only the first three had been filmed. The fourth had been shooting when the show was cancelled and would remain unfinished. Episodes 14, 15, and 16 have not yet been aired in the U.S. however were aired on March 11 and March 18 in the UK on [[ITV2]]. FOX stated that the completed three episodes would air in the future, though they did not give a date. As of October 2013, they have not aired but have been posted on online services such as [[iTunes]] and [[Amazon.com]].\n\n==Episodes==\nThere were 16 episodes in ''Ben and Kate's'' single season.<ref name=\"kondolojy1\"/><ref name=\"FOXFast\">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxfast.com/FoxFast/aspxfiles/TitleDetailsHome.aspx?TitleId=2AA1293F-F533-4C5F-9CB5-172761F0FEE2 |title=View, Screen, Download |publisher=FoxFast.com |date= |accessdate=2013-01-09}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"  style=\"width:100%; margin-right:0;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|No.\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|Title\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|Directed by\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|Written by\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|Original air date\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text-align:center;\"|Production<br />code\n! style=\"background:#00C5CD; color:#fff; text