nuary 9, 2013}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Kate tries to get Maddie in an advanced placement class. Ben finds out that Matt Swan ([[David Hornsby]]), an old college roommate who is now quite wealthy, stole his idea of an extraordinary pizza. BJ's mother, Wendy ([[Jane Seymour (actress)|Jane Seymour]]), visits her.\n |LineColor       = 00C5CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |Title           = Girl Problems\n |DirectedBy      = David Katzenberg\n |WrittenBy       = Matt Fusfeld & Alex Cuthbertson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|1|15}}\n |ProdCode        = 1AVE11\n |Viewers         = 2.20<ref>{{cite web|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|title=Tuesday Final Ratings:'NCIS', 'Off Their Rockers' & 'The New Normal' Adjusted Up|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/01/16/tuesday-final-ratings-ncis-off-their-rockers-the-new-normal-adjusted-up/165524/comment-page-2/#comments|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=January 16, 2013|date=January 16, 2013}}</ref> \n |ShortSummary    = Now that Tommy and Lila are dating, Kate tries to be friends with her, but ends up making matters worse. Ben tries get his idea of a Rail Mall (a train alternative to [[SkyMall]]) funded by Vera ([[Melinda McGraw]]), a businesswoman who is only in business with him for sex.\n |LineColor       = 00C5CD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 13\n |Title           = Bake-Off\n |DirectedBy      = Fred Goss\n |WrittenBy       = Sam Sklaver \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|1|22}}\n |ProdCode        = 1AVE12\n |Viewers         = 2.53<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/01/24/tuesday-final-ratings-parenthood-the-taste-hart-of-dixie-emily-owens-m-d-adjusted-down/166355|title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'Parenthood' & 'New Girl' Adjusted Up; 'The Taste', 'Hart of Dixie' & 'Emily Owens M.D.' Adjusted Down|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=January 24, 2013|accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref> \n |ShortSummary    = Kate tries to move on after breaking up with 