o create a media frenzy, which the district attorney and the mayor want to avoid. Keegan tries to alienate both the judge ([[Mary Kay Place]]) and the women jury members, in order to lose the trial. He also has sex with his client. Ben learns the daughter really did commit said murder. Elsewhere, the mayor discovers his wife's flirtation with Keegan; and the IRS wins a court decision for a huge garnishment of Keegan's salary.\n| LineColor       = 2d525d\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| Title           = Three Strikes\n| DirectedBy      = [[Amy Heckerling]]\n| WrittenBy       = Kit Boss\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|3|06}}\n| ProdCode        = RAK108\n| Viewers         = 3.53<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/03/07/thursday-final-ratings-the-big-bang-theory-once-upon-a-time-in-wonderland-parks-and-recreation-the-millers-two-and-a-half-men-adjusted-down/242882/|title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'The Big Bang Theory', 'Once Upon A Time in Wonderland', 'Parks and Recreation' & 'Elementary' Adjusted Up; 'The Millers' & 'Two and a Half Men' Adjusted Down|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 7, 2014|accessdate=March 7, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Reggie Jarvis ([[Anthony Anderson]]), a friend of Keegan's from [[Alcoholics Anonymous]], is charged with a robbery he didn't commit. It is Jarvis's [[Three-strikes law|third strike felony]]; Keegan must somehow defend him without a plea deal, since the mayor has refused those from Keegan. The clever ploy of insulting the judge to the point of contempt and mistrial does the trick. At his financial and career crossroads, Keegan accepts a job at Ben's corporate law firm.\n| LineColor       = 2d525d\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| Title           = Staple Holes\n| DirectedBy      = [[Adam Arkin]]\n| WrittenBy       = Kevin J. Hynes\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|3|14}}\n| ProdCode        = RAK109\n| Viewers         = 1.82<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/03/17/friday-final-ratings-shark-tank-adjusted-up-dateline-the-neighbors-undercover-boss-enlisted-blue-bloods-adjusted-down/245204/|title=Friday Final Ratings: 'Shark Tank' Adjusted Up, 'Dateline', 'Neighbors', 'Undercover Boss', 'Enlisted' & 'Blue Bloods' Adjusted Down|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Bibel|first=Sara|date=March 17, 2014|accessdate=March 17, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Although Keegan begrudgingly joins Ben's law firm, he likes the perks of the job. He also wins his first case, despite Ben's colleagues' preference for a long drawn-out profitable loss. Elsewhere, Scarlet awaits her nomination for district attorney. The mayor is found dead in his bathroom, from [[erotic asphyxiation|autoerotic asphyxiation]], by ex-chief of police Bernie, who wants to put the blame on Keegan.\n| LineColor       = 2d525d\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| Title           = Hey, Good Looking\n| DirectedBy      = Cherie Nowlan\n| WrittenBy       = Sara Goodman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|3|21}}\n| ProdCode        = RAK110\n| Viewers         = 1.90<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/03/24/friday-final-ratings-shark-tank-hart-of-dixie-adjusted-down/247165/|title=Friday Final Ratings: 'Shark Tank' & '20/20' Adjusted Up; 'Hart of Dixie' Adjusted Down + Final NCAA Basketball Numbers|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|date=March 24, 2014|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Holly Phillips ([[Kate Burton (actress)|Kate Burton]]) is charged with killing her husband, and Keegan appeals to everyone's insecurities during her trial. Later, he is charged with the Mayor's murder when evidence is planted in his apartment. This causes Ben and Scarlet to differ in their opinions of him. Meanwhile, Bruce becomes Maddy's stalker and she needs Keegan's help scaring him away.\n| LineColor       = 2d525d\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| Title           = 50 Shades of Gay\n| DirectedBy      = [[Rosemary Rodriguez]]\n| WrittenBy       = Allison Abner\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|3|28}}\n| ProdCode        = RAK111\n| Viewers         = 1.90<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/03/31/friday-final-ratings-last-man-standing-the-neighbors-dateline-hannibal-hart-of-dixie-adjusted-down/249240/|title=Friday Final Ratings: 'Last Man Standing', 'The Neighbors, 'Dateline' & '20/20' Adjusted Up; 'Hannibal' & 'Hart of Dixie' Adjusted Down & Final Basketball Numbers|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=March 31, 2014|accessdate=March 31, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Jules, the pimp who first introduced Keegan to Mikki, becomes his newest client. He is accused of assaulting a powerful Hollywood agent, and Keegan cannot find witnesses willing to help Jules. Meanwhile, Maddy punches Finn's teacher and former lover; Scarlet's campaign stalls; and David Potter gets more serious with Mikki.\n| LineColor       = 2d525d\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| Title           = Remembrance of Taxis Past\n| DirectedBy      = [[Roxann Dawson]]\n| WrittenBy       = Kit Boss\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2014|4|05}}\n| ProdCode        = RAK112\n| Viewers         = 1.00<ref name=\"Episode1112\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/04/06/tv-ratings-saturday-dateline-nightline-prime-2020-up-48-hours-steady-rake-finale-hit-low/251449/|title=TV Ratings Saturday: 'Dateline', 'Nightline Prime' & '20/20' Up, '48 Hours' Steady, 'Rake' Finale Hit Low|last=Bibel|first=Sara|work=TV by the Numbers|date=April 6, 2014|accessdate=April 6, 2014}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Keegan asks California's ex-governor, Mitch Markham, to provide financial and political support for Scarlet's campaign for district attorney. Meanwhile, Keegan is dumbstruck when Maddy enlists Glenn, a well-known campaign consultant, to liven up Scarlet's campaign, and David Potter, Mikki's fianc\u00e9e, becomes Scarlet's staunchest 