n[[Category:Television series by Fox Entertainment]]\n[[Category:Television series by Universal Television]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 American drama television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Almost Family\n| image                = Almost Family Title Card.jpg\n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| genre                = {{Plain list|\n*[[Drama (film and television)|Drama]] \n}}\n| based_on             = ''[[Sisters (Australian TV series)|Sisters]]'' by Jonathan Gavin & Imogen Banks\n| creator              =\n| developer            = Annie Weisman\n| starring             = {{Plain list|\n* [[Brittany Snow]]\n* [[Megalyn Echikunwoke]]\n* [[Emily Osment]]\n* [[Mo McRae]] \n* Mustafa Elzein\n* [[Victoria Cartagena]]\n* [[Timothy Hutton]]\n<!--Starring cast order is according to original broadcasting credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new starring cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| music                = [[David Schwartz]]\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1<!--Only increment as a new season premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| num_episodes         = 13<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plain list|\n* [[Leslye Headland]]\n* Imogen Banks\n* Sharon Levy\n* Jeni Mulein\n* Annie Weisman\n* [[Jason Katims]]\n}}\n| producer             = {{Plain list|\n* Patrick Ward\n* Lori Keith Douglas\n}}\n| editor               = {{Plain list|\n* Peter Forslund\n* Nancy Morrison\n* Garret Price\n* Mike Weintraub\n}}\n| location             = \n| cinematography       = {{Plain list|\n* Tim Bellen\n* Arthur Africano\n}}\n| camera               = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime              = 43\u201346 minutes\n| company              = {{Plain list|\n* Parasox\n* True Jack Productions\n* Endemol Shine North America\n* Fox Entertainment\n* XOF Productions\n* [[Universal Television]]\n}}\n| network              = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| picture_format       = [[720p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format         =\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2019|10|2}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2020|2|22}}\n| website              = https://www.fox.com/almost-family/\n| website_title        = Official website\n}}\n\n'''''Almost Family''''' is an American [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series based on the Australian television series, ''[[Sisters (Australian TV series)|Sisters]]'', developed by Annie Weisman which aired from October 2, 2019, to February 22, 2020, on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]].<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\"/>\n\nIn March 2020, Fox cancelled the series after one season.<ref name=\"Cancelled\"/>\n\n==Premise==\nWhen it is revealed that [[fertility doctor]] Leon Bechley ([[Timothy Hutton]]) had used his own [[sperm]] to [[In vitro fertilisation|conceive]] at least 100 children throughout his career, Julia Bechley ([[Brittany Snow]]) unites with two of her [[half sibling]]s\u2014including childhood friend Edie Palmer ([[Megalyn Echikunwoke]]), and retired Olympic athlete Roxy Doyle ([[Emily Osment]])\u2014as they deal with issues that have been affecting their lives.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/fox-fall-2019-2020-trailers-dramas-prodigal-son-and-not-just-me-animated-comedy-bless-the-harts-watch-1203213473/|title=Fox Fall 2019-2020 Trailers: Dramas 'Prodigal Son' and 'Not Just Me,' Animated Comedy 'Bless the Harts' (Watch)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Will|last=Thorne|date=May 13, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514111652/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/fox-fall-2019-2020-trailers-dramas-prodigal-son-and-not-just-me-animated-comedy-bless-the-harts-watch-1203213473/|archive-date=May 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n<!--Cast order is according to original broadcasting credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n* [[Brittany Snow]] as Julia Bechley, a communications director for her father's fertility clinic\n* [[Megalyn Echikunwoke]] as Edie Palmer, Julia's former friend and one of Julia's [[half sibling]]s who is a criminal defense attorney\n* [[Emily Osment]] as Roxy Doyle, a retired gymnast and one of Julia's half siblings\n* [[Mo McRae]] as Tim Moore, Edie's husband who is also a criminal defense attorney at the same law firm and Julia's ex-boyfriend\n* Mustafa Elzein as Dr. Isaac Abadi, an employee of the Bechley clinic and Leon's trusted second-in-command\n* [[Victoria Cartagena]] as Amanda Doherty, the woman that Edie is cheating on her husband with and the [[assistant district attorney]] assigned to prosecute Leon\n* [[Timothy Hutton]] as Leon Bechley, a [[fertility doctor]] and Julia's father, accused of fathering dozens of children without his patients' knowledge or consent\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn October 16, 2018, it was announced that Fox had given the production, then titled ''Sisters'', a pilot production commitment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/sisters-drama-fox-australian-tv-series-annie-weisman-jason-katims-endemol-shine-north-america-put-pilot-1202484209/|title='Sisters' Drama Based On Australian TV Series From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims Lands At Fox As Put Pilot|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=October 16, 2018|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513234143/https://deadline.com/2018/10/sisters-drama-fox-australian-tv-series-annie-weisman-jason-katims-endemol-shine-north-america-put-pilot-1202484209/|archive-date=May 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The pilot was written by Annie Weisman who was also set to executive produce alongside [[Jason Katims]], Jeni Mulein, Imogen Banks, Sharon Levy, Leslye Headland (also the director). Production companies involved with the pilot include [[Universal Television]] and [[Fox Entertainment Group|Fox Entertainment]]. On February 13, 2019, the production officially received a pilot order.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/fox-drama-pilot-fannie-weisman-jason-katims-based-on-australian-series-sisters-1202556668/|title=Fox Orders Drama Pilot From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims Based On Australian Series 'Sisters'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=February 13, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730090820/https://deadline.com/2019/02/fox-drama-pilot-fannie-weisman-jason-katims-based-on-australian-series-sisters-1202556668/|archive-date=July 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn May 9, 2019, it was announced that Fox had given the series order.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/fox-orders-drama-series-prodigal-son-deputy-next-weisman-katims-bubble-dramas-1202610963/|title=Fox Picks Up 4 New Drama Series: 'Prodigal Son', 'Deputy', 'NeXt' & Weisman/Katims; What Does It Mean For Network's Bubble Dramas?|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511022247/https://deadline.com/2019/05/fox-orders-drama-series-prodigal-son-deputy-next-weisman-katims-bubble-dramas-1202610963/|archive-date=May 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A few days later, it was announced that the title of the show had been changed to ''Not Just Me''. A day after that, it was announced that the series would premiere in the fall of 2019 and air on Wednesdays at 9:00 P.M.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/fox-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-empire-the-masked-singer-the-orville-last-man-standing-1202613344/|title=Fox Fall 2019-20 Schedule: WWE, NFL, No Live-Action Comedies With 'Last Man Standing' Held, 'Empire' & 'Resident' To Tuesday|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=May 13, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714124325/https://deadline.com/2019/05/fox-fall-2019-20-schedule-upfronts-new-shows-empire-the-masked-singer-the-orville-last-man-standing-1202613344/|archive-date=July 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2019, Fox changed the title from ''Not Just Me'' to ''Almost Family''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Emily Osment\u2019s New FOX Show Gets a Name Change|url=http://www.beautifulballad.org/2019/06/05/emily-osments-new-fox-show-gets-a-name-change/|work=BeautifulBallad|date=June 5, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607003112/http://www.beautifulballad.org/2019/06/05/emily-osments-new-fox-show-gets-a-name-change/|archive-date=June 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The series debuted on October 2, 2019.<ref name=\"SeriesPremiereDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/fox-sets-fall-premiere-dates-emmys-9-1-1-the-masked-singer-empire-more-1202637086/|title=Fox Sets Fall Premiere Dates: Emmys Kick Off The Week, '9-1-1', 'The Masked Singer', 'Empire', More|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=June 24, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819200819/https://deadline.com/2019/06/fox-sets-fall-premiere-dates-emmys-9-1-1-the-masked-singer-empire-more-1202637086/|archive-date=August 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On March 2, 2020, the series was cancelled after one season.<ref name=\"Cancelled\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/almost-family-canceled-fox-1203521583/|title=\u2018Almost Family\u2019 Canceled After One Season at Fox|last=Thorne|first=Will|date=March 2, 2020|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302234330/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/almost-family-canceled-fox-1203521583/|archive-date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Brittany Snow]] and [[Megalyn Echikunwoke]] had been cast in the pilot's lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/brittany-snow-star-fox-drama-pilot-from-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202565179/|title=Brittany Snow To Star In Fox's Drama Pilot From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=February 25, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513220353/https://deadline.com/2019/02/brittany-snow-star-fox-drama-pilot-from-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202565179/|archive-date=May 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/megalyn-echikunwoke-cast-fox-drama-pilot-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202565521/|title=Megalyn Echikunwoke To Star In Fox's Drama Pilot From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=February 26, 2019|website=Deadline Hollywood|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513220351/https://deadline.com/2019/02/megalyn-echikunwoke-cast-fox-drama-pilot-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202565521/|archive-date=May 13, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref> In March 2019, it was reported that [[Emily Osment]] and [[Victoria Cartagena]] had joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/emily-osment-star-fox-drama-pilot-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202569314/|title=Emily Osment To Star In Fox's Drama Pilot From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=March 4, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804031506/https://deadline.com/2019/03/emily-osment-star-fox-drama-pilot-annie-weisman-jason-katims-1202569314/|archive-date=August 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/victoria-cartagena-cast-in-foxs-drama-pilot-from-annie-weisman-jason-katims-mark-moses-in-deputy-1202583931/|title=Victoria Cartagena Cast In Fox's Drama Pilot From Annie Weisman & Jason Katims; Mark Moses In 'Deputy'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=March 28, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811181216/https://deadline.com/2019/03/victoria-cartagena-cast-in-foxs-drama-pilot-from-annie-weisman-jason-katims-mark-moses-in-deputy-1202583931/|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#D3CEC6|overall= |title= |titleR=<ref name=\"TFC\"/> |director= |writer= |writerT=Teleplay by |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Almost Family \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/almost-family/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref> |country=U.S. |viewers= |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Leslye Headland]]\n |WrittenBy       = Annie Weisman\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|2}}\n |Viewers         = 2.73<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-oct-2-2019/|title='Chicago Med,' 'The Masked Singer' adjust up, 'Single Parents,' 'Almost Family' adjust down: Wednesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|date=October 3, 2019|accessdate=October 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003210110/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-oct-2-2019/|archive-date=October 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficiall